    {
      "id": "sybil_9_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_9",
      "description": "Available is a mechanically sound 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the high-revving S54B32 inline-six engine. This unit utilizes individual throttle bodies and Double VANOS to deliver a linear power band peaking at 7,900 RPM. Power is routed through a Getrag 6-speed manual gearbox to a variable M-differential lock. Critical preventative maintenance has been addressed, including rod bearing replacement and a reinforced rear subframe to mitigate common chassis fatigue. The suspension retains its factory-spec geometry with upgraded dampers for improved rebound control. This is a driver-focused example with crisp throttle response and a rigid, communicative chassis, showing only minor cosmetic wear expected of a well-maintained performance machine.",
      "price": 34500.0,
